Meet <b>Jaysen</b>, our Citizen of the Week!<br><br>Jaysen moved to Millsberry on February 16, 2007&mdash;just a couple months ago! In such a short time, he has already proved what a great addition he is to the community. This athletic, charming citizen has quickly made his Golden Valley home at <a href='/home/?user=jaysen01440'>45040-B Wells Road</a> into a comfortable, cozy place to hang out.<br><br>Among his athletic interests are football and baseball, but recently he's shown that he has a knack for basketball and skateboarding too! Jaysen hopes to try his hand at hockey soon, and is learning to feel at home on the ice. With his good sense of balance and determination, he's sure to be a star skater in no time. <br><br>When not playing sports, he focuses on doing well in school and meeting more of his classmates. He has made some friends in the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/lab/">Millsberry Academy lab</a>, where his interest in physics has grown thanks to Mr. Fort's excellent mentoring. <br><br>When he's staying late at school finishing projects, you'll find him listening to his favorite jazz station, which helps him get things done and relaxes him. Thanks for being a good citizen, Jaysen, and congrats on being named Citizen of the Week!</div>
